{
  "stem": "27340.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And as, in fact, the danger of Nazis, and especially in 1933 when Hitler came to power, became fairly obvious, then we in fact became more Jewish-minded as well, because we obviously became a-- a member, or we became a family of a minority, of an oppressed minority.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As far as I know, my parents, yes, and my grandparents were always members of the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They must have paid their dues, I'm quite convinced.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as such, we lived a very normal sort of civil type of life.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The-- my parents belonged to a very large synagogue in Breslau, but--but without any doubt the largest of its kind in the city.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was huge.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think it accommodated something like 2 to 3,000 congregants.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I do remember on the high holidays that that synagogue was chock-a-block full.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It always impressed me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was in the middle of town, fairly close to a police headquarters, in fact, next door to a police headquarters, and not too far away from the royal residence where Prussian kings used to live when they came to the city.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was one of the main buildings in Breslau, in so far that whenever you went for a walk around the town or in the town, wherever there was an opportunity to see the skyline of the city, invariably the new synagogue as it was called, the [NON-ENGLISH] was invariably indicated.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So there was the town hall and there was a [NON-ENGLISH], a special building that was built in Breslau to celebrate a century of whatever it was.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I really don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the new synagogue, together with also the cathedral and one or two other prominent churches, always figured on those plates.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
